{"TopicId":196282,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"convenient ways to put the visual focus on kerbin","CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-13T22:38:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-13T22:38:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhen i want to fin tune a manuever around a planet, i set the visual focus on the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthen i must go back to looking at my ship around kerbin. and that\u0027s not as easy, because kerbin orbit is so cluttered with stuff than i cannot select the planet. wherever i click, the game thinks i am trying to pick a satellite, or a piece of another orbit. sometimes i do remove everything from the map view. sometimes i click at random until i can get back on track, i\u0027m not sure how. is there any better way?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Grogs","CreatedById":195516,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-13T22:55:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Tab key will cycle between different focuses. It goes in order from the ship to the maneuver node (if any), then the sun, Moho, Eve, etc. Also, the \u0060 key in the upper left of the keyboard will reset the focus to your ship if you need to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-13T23:49:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat Grogs said, TAB is the best solution, i have a problem though i dont have the cycle back button, its lost somewhere, since i changed buttons \u003Cspan\u003E:p .\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-13T23:57:18Z\u0022 title=\u002208/13/2020 11:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 13, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-14T00:26:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223837648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597359339\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Grogs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Grogs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Tab key will cycle between different focuses. It goes in order from the ship to the maneuver node (if any), then the sun, Moho, Eve, etc. Also, the \u0060 key in the upper left of the keyboard will reset the focus to your ship if you need to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni knew there must be a function for it somewhere\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MAFman","CreatedById":101780,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-14T02:50:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found that the tilde key ~ resets the focus on the active vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T06:16:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also go into the tracking station and hide items. That can clean things up a bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T10:46:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838460\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597472207\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also go into the tracking station and hide items. That can clean things up a bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s possible in normal map view, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T16:08:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223837675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597362554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/14/2020 at 1:49 AM, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni have a problem though i dont have the cycle back button, its lost somewhere, since i changed buttons \u003Cspan\u003E:p .\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably because the factory-default key for that is \u0027Backspace\u0027, which will also trigger whatever actions you placed in the Abort action group.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Grogs","CreatedById":195516,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T18:23:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838634\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597507692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably because the factory-default key for that is \u0027Backspace\u0027, which will also trigger whatever actions you placed in the Abort action group.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy abort key is F9. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T18:38:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838707\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597515783\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Grogs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Grogs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy abort key is F9. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhats your quickload key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDunno hitting backspace hard brings some pleasure/immersion when aborting \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T18:50:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223837675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597362554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/14/2020 at 1:49 AM, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni have a problem though i dont have the cycle back button, its lost somewhere, since i changed buttons \u003Cspan\u003E:p .\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838634\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597507692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably because the factory-default key for that is \u0027Backspace\u0027, which will also trigger whatever actions you placed in the Abort action group.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I had my coffee yet when I typed this. Cycle back is not Backspace by default.... it\u0027s Shift-Tab. Which still explains why it\u0027s one of the first key assignments changed, as trying to cycle back inevitably (Shift!) throttles up your engines if you haven\u0027t deactivated or locked them, and the next moment you\u0027re wondering why your orbit is changing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Grogs","CreatedById":195516,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T18:56:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838717\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597516698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhats your quickload key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDunno hitting backspace hard brings some pleasure/immersion when aborting \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was supposed to be a joke - my \u0027abort\u0027 sequence if the engines suddenly start pointing upwards is to quickload or revert.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T19:09:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838733\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597517775\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Grogs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Grogs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was supposed to be a joke - my \u0027abort\u0027 sequence if the engines suddenly start pointing upwards is to quickload or revert.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nops, missed that one\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E good one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}